{"questionId":"1251252","questionHtml":"<p>The points X and Y are in a uniform electric field of strength <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>E</mi></math>. The distance OX is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math> and the&nbsp;distance OY is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi></math>.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\">&nbsp;<img src=\"__IMG__/aa835459d7eb8042f760f8f78d1f45bbfc535cc8.png\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p>What is the magnitude of the change in electric potential between X and Y?</p>\n<p>A.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>E</mi><mi>x</mi></math></p>\n<p>B.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>E</mi><mi>y</mi></math></p>\n<p>C.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>E</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>+</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>y</mi><mo>)</mo></math></p>\n<p>D.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>E</mi><msqrt><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>+</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><msup><mi>y</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></msqrt></math></p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>A</p>","meta":{"questionId":"1251252","referenceCode":"21M.1A.HL.TZ2.31","subjectId":"59-dp-physics-first-assessment-2025","title":"The points X and Y are in a uniform electric field of strength E. The distance OX is x and the distance OY is y. What is the magnitude of the change in electric potential between X","paper":"1A","level":"HL","questionNumber":"31","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["D. Fields","D.2 Electric and magnetic fields"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}